1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL FLEXIBILITY TO LOCAL BOARDS OF
3 EDUCATION IN ADOPTING THE SCHOOL CALENDAR.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 115C-84.2 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 115C-84.2. School calendar.
7 …
8 (a2) Report on School Start and End Dates. – As part of the reporting requirements under
9 the Uniform Education Reporting System pursuant to G.S. 115C-12(18), annually by April 1
10 each local board of education shall report to the Superintendent of Public Instruction and the
11 State Board of Education on the start and end dates of the instructional calendar for students for
12 the next academic year. The local board of education shall report this information for each school
13 under the control of that board and shall identify the statutory exception authorizing an earlier
14 start date for all schools that start earlier than the Monday closest to August 26.authority relied
15 upon to set the dates.
16 …
17 (d) Opening and Closing Dates. – Local boards of education shall determine the dates of
18 adopt a school calendar setting the opening and closing dates for the public schools under that
19 complies with subdivision (a)(1) of this section. Except for year-round schools, the section and
20 one of the following:
21 (1) The opening date for students shall be is no earlier than the Monday closest to
22 August 26, and the closing date for students shall be is no later than the Friday
23 closest to June 11. On a showing of good cause, the State Board of Education
24 may allow the local board of education to set an opening date no earlier than
25 the Monday closest to August 19.
26 (2) The opening for students is no earlier than the Monday closest to August 19,
27 so long as there are an equal number of days in the fall and spring semesters,
28 and the closing date for students is no later than the Friday immediately
29 preceding the last Monday in May.
30 (d1) Calendar Revision. – Notwithstanding the closing date adopted in conformance with
31 subsection (d) of this section, a local board of education may, with approval of the State Board
32 of Education, revise the scheduled closing date for students if a school experiences closures
33 caused by severe weather, energy shortages, power failures, or emergencies, and additional
34 instructional time is needed to comply with minimum requirements for instructional days or
35 hours.
